---
layout: layouts/tool.njk
title: Case Converter - Change Text Case Online (Upper, Lower, Title)
description: Free online case converter. Convert text to UPPERCASE, lowercase, Title Case, Sentence case, camelCase, snake_case, kebab-case and more. Instant conversion.
keywords: case converter, uppercase to lowercase, lowercase to uppercase, title case converter, sentence case, camelCase, snake_case, kebab-case, text case changer
permalink: /tools/case-converter/
toolId: case-converter
toolJs: case-converter.js
ogImage: case-converter.jpg
---
{% set toolData = tools | findById(toolId) %}

{% block schema %}
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "{{ site.url }}/"},
    {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Tools", "item": "{{ site.url }}/#tools"},
    {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "{{ toolData.name }}", "item": "{{ site.url }}{{ page.url }}"}
  ]
}
</script>
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebApplication",
  "name": "{{ toolData.fullName }}",
  "description": "{{ description }}",
  "url": "{{ site.url }}{{ page.url }}",
  "applicationCategory": "UtilityApplication",
  "operatingSystem": "Any",
  "browserRequirements": "Requires JavaScript",
  "offers": {"@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "USD"},
  "featureList": ["UPPERCASE conversion", "lowercase conversion", "Title Case", "Sentence case", "camelCase", "snake_case", "kebab-case", "CONSTANT_CASE"],
  "author": {"@type": "Organization", "name": "{{ site.name }}", "url": "{{ site.url }}"}
}
</script>
{% endblock %}

{% block head %}
<style>
  .case-buttons {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(140px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-2);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .case-btn {
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text);
    transition: all var(--transition-fast);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .case-btn:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-primary);
    background: var(--color-primary-light);
  }
  .case-btn.active {
    border-color: var(--color-primary);
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: white;
  }
  .case-example {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-top: var(--space-1);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }
  .text-area {
    width: 100%;
    min-height: 180px;
    padding: var(--space-4);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    background: var(--color-bg);
    color: var(--color-text);
    resize: vertical;
  }
  .text-area:focus {
    outline: none;
    border-color: var(--color-primary);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--color-primary-light);
  }
  .text-area-label {
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    display: block;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .text-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
</style>
{% endblock %}

<div class="tool-container">
  <!-- Case Conversion Buttons -->
  <div class="case-buttons" role="group" aria-label="Case conversion options">
    <button class="case-btn" data-case="upper">
      UPPERCASE
      <div class="case-example">HELLO WORLD</div>
    </button>
    <button class="case-btn" data-case="lower">
      lowercase
      <div class="case-example">hello world</div>
    </button>
    <button class="case-btn" data-case="title">
      Title Case
      <div class="case-example">Hello World</div>
    </button>
    <button class="case-btn" data-case="sentence">
      Sentence case
      <div class="case-example">Hello world. New sentence.</div>
    </button>
    <button class="case-btn" data-case="camel">
      camelCase
      <div class="case-example">helloWorld</div>
    </button>
    <button class="case-btn" data-case="pascal">
      PascalCase
      <div class="case-example">HelloWorld</div>
    </button>
    <button class="case-btn" data-case="snake">
      snake_case
      <div class="case-example">hello_world</div>
    </button>
    <button class="case-btn" data-case="kebab">
      kebab-case
      <div class="case-example">hello-world</div>
    </button>
    <button class="case-btn" data-case="constant">
      CONSTANT_CASE
      <div class="case-example">HELLO_WORLD</div>
    </button>
    <button class="case-btn" data-case="dot">
      dot.case
      <div class="case-example">hello.world</div>
    </button>
    <button class="case-btn" data-case="toggle">
      tOGGLE cASE
      <div class="case-example">hELLO wORLD</div>
    </button>
    <button class="case-btn" data-case="alternating">
      AlTeRnAtInG
      <div class="case-example">HeLlO wOrLd</div>
    </button>
  </div>

  <!-- Input Text -->
  <div class="text-section">
    <label for="input-text" class="text-area-label">Input Text</label>
    <textarea
      id="input-text"
      class="text-area"
      placeholder="Type or paste your text here..."
      aria-label="Input text to convert"
    ></textarea>
  </div>

  <!-- Output Text -->
  <div class="text-section">
    <label for="output-text" class="text-area-label">Converted Text</label>
    <textarea
      id="output-text"
      class="text-area"
      readonly
      placeholder="Converted text will appear here..."
      aria-label="Converted output text"
    ></textarea>
  </div>

  <!-- Actions -->
  <div class="tool-actions">
    <button id="copy-output" class="btn btn-primary">Copy Result</button>
    <button id="swap-text" class="btn btn-secondary">Swap Input/Output</button>
    <button id="clear-all" class="btn btn-ghost">Clear</button>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="content-section">
  <h2>How to Use</h2>
  <div class="steps">
    <div class="step"><div class="step-number">1</div><div class="step-content"><h3>Enter Your Text</h3><p>Type or paste the text you want to convert into the input field.</p></div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-number">2</div><div class="step-content"><h3>Choose a Case Style</h3><p>Click on any case conversion button to transform your text.</p></div></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="step-number">3</div><div class="step-content"><h3>Copy the Result</h3><p>Click "Copy Result" to copy the converted text to your clipboard.</p></div></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="content-section">
  <h2>Case Styles Explained</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>UPPERCASE</strong> - All letters become capital letters</li>
    <li><strong>lowercase</strong> - All letters become small letters</li>
    <li><strong>Title Case</strong> - First letter of each word is capitalized</li>
    <li><strong>Sentence case</strong> - First letter of each sentence is capitalized</li>
    <li><strong>camelCase</strong> - No spaces, first word lowercase, subsequent words capitalized</li>
    <li><strong>PascalCase</strong> - No spaces, all words start with capital letter</li>
    <li><strong>snake_case</strong> - Words separated by underscores, all lowercase</li>
    <li><strong>kebab-case</strong> - Words separated by hyphens, all lowercase</li>
    <li><strong>CONSTANT_CASE</strong> - Words separated by underscores, all uppercase</li>
    <li><strong>dot.case</strong> - Words separated by dots, all lowercase</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="content-section">
  <h2>FAQ</h2>
  <div class="faq-list">
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-question">What is case conversion?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer"><p>Case conversion changes the capitalization of text. For example, converting "Hello World" to "HELLO WORLD" is an uppercase conversion.</p></div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-question">When should I use camelCase vs snake_case?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer"><p>camelCase is commonly used in JavaScript and Java. snake_case is preferred in Python and Ruby. kebab-case is used for URLs and CSS class names.</p></div>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary class="faq-question">Is my text stored anywhere?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. All conversion happens in your browser. Your text never leaves your device.</p></div>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

